This folder contains the KV260 smartcamera Vitis platform. The smartcamera
platform supports the following multimedia peripherals and interfaces:

1. MIPI CSI PL interface connected to the AR1335 IAS image sensor and  on-board
   AP1302 ISP.

2. DisplayPort and HDMI Tx via the PS DP interface and on-board DP splitter.

3. USB 3.0 PS interface for connecting a UVC compliant USB webcam.

4. Hardened Video Codec Unit (VCU) consisting of H264/H265 encoder and decoder.

5. I2S audio Rx and Tx PL interfaces via optional PMOD.

6. Ethernet PS interface for video streaming protocols like RTSP.

7. SD card PS interface for video file playback and storage.


Open the Vivado design:
***********************

To open the underlying Vivado platform design from the provided XSA file, run
the following command from the Vivado tcl console:

$ open_hw_platform xilinx_kv260_smartcamera_202022_1/hw/kv260_smartcamera.xsa

You can now modify the block design and run Vivado implementation and bitstream
generation.

To write out a new extensible platform XSA file, run the following command from
the Vivado tcl console:

$ write_hw_platform -force -include_bit -file kv260_smartcamera.xsa

The new XSA file can now be used replacing the existing XSA file in the Vitis
platform or as hardware handoff file inside the Petalinux project.

